1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:05,240
If you ever need to include special characters like quotation marks or adding a new line,

2

00:00:05,240  -->  00:00:07,960
such as an Enter, into the string,

3

00:00:07,960  -->  00:00:11,980
you can use the backslash character as an escape character.

4

00:00:11,980  -->  00:00:16,180
You might not have ever needed to use this special backslash character before,

5

00:00:16,180  -->  00:00:20,180
but it is a very handy one to have in your back pocket.

6

00:00:20,180  -->  00:00:24,560
For example, let's say that you want to break up text into two lines,

7

00:00:24,560  -->  00:00:26,340
but it is the same string.

8

00:00:26,340  -->  00:00:29,560
You can use the handy backslash character to put

9

00:00:29,560  -->  00:00:33,440
the part after the backslash onto a second line.

10

00:00:33,440  -->  00:00:37,700
Otherwise, it would all be on one line without that special symbol.

11

00:00:37,700  -->  00:00:41,030
Let's see what this looks like in practice.

12

00:00:41,060  -->  00:00:45,900
Let's talk about escaping using the backslash character.

13

